4 and to the extent, and only to the extent, necessary to
5 effectuate this intent, the governor may modify the strict
6 provisions of this Act, but shall promptly report any
7 modification with reasons therefor to the legislature at its
8 next session thereafter for review by the legislature.
9 SECTION 4. This Act shall take effect on July 1, 2026;
10 provided that section 2 shall take effect retroactively on
11 June 30, 2026.
